        <scopecontent id="ref10">
            <head>Scope and Content of Collection</head>
            <p>Drafts and galleys of the book compiled by G. I. Gay, titled <title altrender="italic">Public Relations of the Commission for Relief in Belgium : Documents</title> (Stanford, 1929) and correspondence relating to relief activities of the Commission for Relief in Belgium during World War I. Includes three paintings on flour sacks.</p>
